value.0: Welcome to [server].  Before you begin there are some things which need to be done.  It will take a few minutes to configure your PC, but it will be worth it in the end.  USE THIS ONLY IF YOU WANT TO CONFIGURE YOUR ALIGNMENT VIA CONVO CHOICES AND IF YOU ARE MAKING A NEW PC.  OTHERWISE DO NOT SPEAK TO THIS NPC...JUST ASK FIONN ABOUT HIS PC'S NEW ALIGNMENT.

First you will need to go through a few questions to work out your alignment, then you will have a chance to purchase some gear, learn about the server you are going to start on, and then you'll be ready.
The following twelve questions are designed to determine your alignment.  Not every question will have an answer which suits you, so choose the closest.
Family Elders are expressing disapproval of you to the rest of the family.  What do you do?
Do you respect the leaders of your family?
A powerful but corrupt judge offers you wealth if you'll testify against a friend of yours.  What do you do?
How do you view lifelong commitment to a single romantic partner?
Your community is threatened with invasion.  What do you do?
Do you respect the laws and authorities in the community?
You country is wracked with famine.  What do you do?
What do you think of the rulers of the land?
You accidently commit a crime.  What do you do?
What is the best use of wealth?
What is the best path to wealth?

You have now completed your alignment test and your alignment is set at  <Alignment>  If you disagree with this, or would like it changed, contact a DM and explain how your character is not of this alignment, or change it through IC actions
You now have a chance to purchase some gear, after that you may ask the other NPCs in the area about the server, before choosing which starting location you wish to begin at.
